{# Inline meta-refresh + JS redirect so this page stays a thin
   forwarder. /app/backup/ is the canonical place to take a backup or
   download the active profile alone — Export used to do the exact
   same thing, so it's been merged. The visible card is a fallback
   for users who arrive with JS off (extremely rare for the app shell
   but cheap to support). #}
<meta http-equiv="refresh" content="0; url=/app/backup/">
<div class="app-page" x-data x-init="window.location.replace('/app/backup/')">
  <header class="app-page__header">
    <h1 class="app-page__title">Export moved to Backup</h1>
  </header>
  <section class="card">
    <p class="card__body">
      Export and Backup did the same thing (download a JSON snapshot of your profile), so they've been merged. <a href="/app/backup/">Continue to /app/backup/</a> — that's the canonical place to take a backup or download the active profile alone.
    </p>
    <p class="card__body" style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: var(--fs-sm);">
      You should be redirected automatically. If you aren't, click the link above.
    </p>
  </section>
</div>
